   "source": [
    "We will define a function (function1) that \n",
    "<p>1).takes a series of neighbourhood names</p>\n",
    "<p>2).combines them properly with commas in between names, taking care that there is no comma after the last name.</p>\n",
    "    We will define a second function that:\n",
    "<p>1).takes the list of Borough associated with a postcode</p>\n",
    "<p>2).verifies that the postcode is completely contained within the Borough. If it is not, launch an exception. If it is, return the name of the Borough.</p>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def function1(x):\n",
    "    formatted_string = \"\"\n",
    "    for k in range(len(x)-1):\n",
    "        formatted_string = formatted_string + x.iloc[k] + \", \"\n",
    "    formatted_string = formatted_string + x.iloc[-1]\n",
    "    return formatted_string\n",
    "\n",
    "def function2(x):\n",
    "    ref = x.iloc[0]\n",
    "    for j in range(1, len(x)):\n",
    "        if ref != x.iloc[j]:\n",
    "            for j in x:\n",
    "                print(x)\n",
    "            raise Exception(\"The postcode is not completely contained within the Borough\")\n",
    "    return ref"
   ]
  },
